Here's a comprehensive list of kubectl commands, organized by category.
Basic / Getting Info

kubectl get — list resources
kubectl describe — detailed info about a resource
kubectl explain — documentation for a resource/field
kubectl api-resources — list supported resource types
kubectl api-versions — list supported API versions
kubectl version — client/server version
kubectl cluster-info — cluster endpoint info
kubectl config — manage kubeconfig (view, set-context, use-context, current-context)

Create / Apply

kubectl create — create resource from file/stdin
kubectl apply — declarative create/update
kubectl run — create and run a pod
kubectl expose — create a Service for a resource
kubectl set — change resource fields (image, resources, env, selector)
kubectl autoscale — create an HPA

Edit / Update

kubectl edit — edit resource in editor
kubectl patch — partial update (strategic/JSON merge)
kubectl replace — replace resource from file
kubectl scale — change replica count
kubectl rollout — manage rollouts (status, history, undo, restart, pause, resume)
kubectl label — add/update/remove labels
kubectl annotate — add/update/remove annotations

Delete

kubectl delete — delete resources

Debugging / Interaction

kubectl logs — print container logs (-f follow, --previous)
kubectl exec — run command in a container
kubectl attach — attach to a running container
kubectl port-forward — forward local port to a pod/service
kubectl proxy — proxy to the API server
kubectl cp — copy files to/from containers
kubectl debug — create debugging containers/ephemeral containers
kubectl top — resource usage (nodes, pods) — needs Metrics Server
kubectl events — list events

Cluster / Node Management

kubectl cordon — mark node unschedulable
kubectl uncordon — mark node schedulable
kubectl drain — safely evict pods from a node
kubectl taint — update node taints
kubectl certificate — approve/deny CSRs

Auth / RBAC

kubectl auth can-i — check permissions
kubectl auth reconcile — reconcile RBAC rules
kubectl create role / create clusterrole
kubectl create rolebinding / create clusterrolebinding
kubectl create serviceaccount

Output / Misc

kubectl wait — wait for a condition
kubectl diff — diff live vs would-be applied config
kubectl kustomize — build a kustomization
kubectl apply -k — apply a kustomization
kubectl completion — shell autocompletion
kubectl plugin — manage kubectl plugins (krew)
kubectl options — global flags

Common Useful Flags

-n <namespace> / --all-namespaces (-A)
-o yaml | json | wide | name | jsonpath=... | custom-columns=...
-l <label-selector> (label filter)
--field-selector
-f <file> (from file)
--dry-run=client|server
-w (watch)

kubeadm (cluster lifecycle)

kubeadm init — bootstrap control plane
kubeadm join — join a node
kubeadm reset — undo init/join
kubeadm upgrade — upgrade cluster
kubeadm token — manage join tokens
kubeadm certs — manage certificates